/******************************************************************************
 Question 2: Ludo King 

Write a Java program to find the winner of a Ludo game based on points scored by three players.

The program should:

Read Alexâ€™s points

Read Nikilâ€™s points

Read Samâ€™s points

ğŸ” Validation rules:

If any playerâ€™s points are less than 0 or greater than 50, print

<points> is an invalid number


and terminate the program.

ğŸ† Winner rules:

If Alex has the highest points â†’ print

Alex scored <points> points and won the game


If Nikil has the highest points â†’ print

Nikil scored <points> points and won the game


Otherwise, Sam is the winner.

*******************************************************************************/

import java.util.*;
public class Main
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
	    System.out.println("Enter Alex's points: ");
	    int A_points = sc.nextInt();
	    if (A_points > 50 || A_points < 0){
	        System.out.println(A_points+" is an invalid number");
	        System.exit(1);
	    }
	    System.out.println("Enter Nikil's points: ");
	    int N_points = sc.nextInt();
	    if (N_points > 50 || N_points < 0){
	        System.out.println(N_points+" is an invalid number");
	        System.exit(1);
	    }
	    System.out.println("Enter Sam's points: ");
	    int S_points = sc.nextInt();
	    if (S_points > 50 || S_points < 0){
	        System.out.println(S_points+" is an invalid number");
	        System.exit(1);
	    }
	    if (A_points > N_points && A_points > S_points){
	        System.out.println("Alex scored " +A_points+ " points and won the game");
	    }
	    else if (N_points > A_points && N_points > S_points){
	        System.out.println("Nikhil scored " +N_points+ " points and won the game");
	    }
	    else{
	         System.out.println("Sam scored " +S_points+ " points and won the game");
	    }
	    
	    
		
	}
}
